Huge fire is burning houses at Kijiji slum in Lang'ata, Nairobi. Efforts to put out the Sunday evening inferno that has destroyed structures at the slum next to Southlands Estate are ongoing.   Fire extinguishers are finding it difficult to access the scene due to congestion of houses. Meanwhile, no casualties have been reported. Residents say the fire started at around 7:30pm. Mr, Pius Masai, the Deputy Director National Disaster Management Unit's Communication Officer, has said four fire engines are battling the inferno and he has asked for more reinforcement. More follows  